In a small mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with milk. Stir until smooth. Stir in raisins. Spread in a greased 8-in. square baking pan. Combine brown sugar and cold water; pour over batter. Bake at 350 degrees F for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.